the capital and operational economics of gbe and gbe services in metro and regional ethernet networks view more  family service delivery switches these costeffective and efficient service delivery switches are available with a range of physical ports of up to gbe they’re purposebuilt to fit numerous small medium and large customer sites as well as multitenant office and residential buildings mounting options include rack wall pole or strand with appropriate enclosures and temperature ranges to solve your unique challenges  family service aggregation switches these switches provide aggregation to efficiently fill higher capacity links within both the metro access and aggregation tiers minimizing the number of router assets required in the core they offer stateoftheart oam and qos capabilities which eliminate significant complexity and cost and can be deployed in a wide variety of locations they also share the same operating system with all of our packet networking products pluggable transceiver family ciena’s pluggable transceiver family allows a flexible payasyougrow deployment model when adding specific functions to our packet networking products traditional tdm services for example can be mapped onto a packetbased infrastructure benefiting from its low costpoint while still maintaining the stringent timing and resilience required by the service the end result new and renewed revenue streams virtualization software ciena’s network functions virtualization infrastructure nfvi is purposebuilt for the distributed nfv use case now service providers can rapidly capture new revenue by rolling out virtualized services to enterprises at the speed of the cloud it includes softwarebased routing encryption and wan optimization deploy a complete dnfv solution in an instant leverage openness explore an open ecosystem to deliver dnfv services view more related resources brochure packet networking products white paper webscale metro ethernet networks video chalk talk tdmtopackets