ical backbone from public sector control of the national science foundation to private companies ciena began working with sprint – an earlier carrier of internet traffic – to develop highcapacity fiber optic transmission systems called dense wave division multiplexing dwdm  the outcome of their effort was the first commercial dense wave division multiplexing system with it the capacity increased sprints nationwide alldigital fiberoptic network by a stunning  percent sprint therefore became the worlds largest carrier of internet traffic with success from sprint and others cienas firstyear sales were the highest ever recorded by a startup in february  ciena pulled off the biggest initial public offering of a startup company ever with a firstday valuation of  billion subsequently goldman sachs in a research note commented on the records set by ciena  steepest revenue ramp for any company in history  most profitable company ever in its first year of product shipments and  largest market capitalization of any new ipo by  ciena had achieved annual revenues of  billion and a marketing capitalization of nearly  billion despite setbacks along the way ciena continued to grow over the next few years by both introducing new products and by acquiring companies such as lightera optical switches and omnia local access equipment with a broader product line cienas customer base had grown from a small handful to  companies as network operators continued building their systems in  ciena announced the multiwave metro optical transport solution which allowed metropolitan area networks to deliver particular frequencies to individual customer premises by june  cienas stock had soared to  per share giving it a market capitalization exceeding  billion sales of the companys new line of products prompted the investor optimism though some analysts were beginning to wonder whether the us fiber optic network had been overbuilt the customer list continued to grow as it approached  names market downturn and diversificationedit during  the telecommunications market went through a severe downturn and the segment that included cienas optical networking equipment fell by nearly  to  billion and in  cienas revenues had declined  to  million to address the firms challenges gary smith previously president and head of sales was named ceo in may  and patrick nettles ceo since  became executive chairman gary smith ciena ceo over the next few years ciena regrouped by expanding its product portfolio to include a broader range of advanced networking solutions including optical switching new generation hybrid gear and ethernet technologies ciena accomplished its diversification effort with internal development as well as a series of acquisitions and strategic partnerships by  ciena had purchased a total of  firms half prior to the downturn with an aggregate value of over  billion with a broader range of offerings ciena was able both to offer its existing customers a wider range of solutions as well as compete for new customers in additional segments and regions the network specialistedit in late  ciena refreshed its branding with the tagline the network specialist to reflect additional capabilities in optical transport and switching cienas diversification strategy and numerous acquisitions were accompanied by its ability to integrate new products and technology advances this success was in contrast to many of its rivals such as nortel alcatel lucent and others that struggled cienas acquisition historyedit company acquired closed date approximate value us million teraxion feb    cyan aug    nortel metro ethernet networks mar    world wide packets mar    internet photonics may    catena networks may    akara sep    wavesmith networks june    oni systems june    cyras mar    omnia communications july    lightera networks mar    terabit apr    alta telecom feb    astracom dec    in  ciena bought from nortel networks its optical networking and carrier ethernet business for  million this acquisition doubled cienas size and increased its customer base to over  on may   ciena announced a definitive agreement to acquire cyan  the cyan acquisition was completed on august    see alsoedit companies portal list of companies in the united states list of sp  companies referencesedit  morgenson gretchen ciena corporation companies new york times archived from the original on  november  retrieved  november    history of ciena pdf   ciena corp moving hq to station ridge in hanover citybizlist baltimore citybizlist   ciena reports fiscal first quarter  financial results ciena corp   ciena  annual report pdf ciena corp   httplwww secgoviarchivesedgardata   txt  httponlinewsj comarticlesb  html  a b newsroom  press releases  ciena wwwcienacom retrieved  may    a b mack toni  october  forbes httpwwwforbescomforbesahtml  missing or empty title help  httpsaresudsicnrsfrimgpdfdwdmcienapdf  ciena corp built on dreams risks decision shareholders will vote friday on the sale of the linthicum telecommunications company one of the most successful us startups retrieved  may    henry mary july   ciena corporation – breaking the bandwidth barrier goldman sachs us research report  ciena  a network strategy and technology company  ciena cienacom retrieved  may    a b c history of ciena corporation – fundinguniverse wwwfundinguniversecom retrieved  may    history of ciena ciena corp retrieved nov   from ciena website  a b moritz scott march   cienas secret weapon diversification forbes magazine retrieved nov    smith gary june   tenacity and teamwork the new york times retrieved nov    ciena website retrieved dec     retrieved september th  external linksedit official site retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlecienaoldid categories cienacompanies listed on the new york stock exchangecompanies formerly listed on nasdaqcompanies based in anne arundel county marylandnetworking companies of the united statesnetworking hardware companiestelecommunications equipme